object.script:
a = false b = 0 c = 0 function onTick() a = input.getBool(1)
if a and c < 56 then c = c+1 elseif not a and c > 0 then c = c-1 end
if c > 0 and c < 48 then b = 0.53 elseif c > 48 and c < 44 then b = 0.57 elseif c > 44 then b = 0.55 else b = 0 end
output.setNumber(1, b) end

t = 120 -- t = timer. 120 = 2 seconds h = true -- h = Hatch p1 = 0 p2 = 0 p3 = 1 t1 = 1 function onTick() r = input.getBool(1) -- r = Retreat Landing Gears
if r and t < 120 then t = t-1 elseif not r and t > 120 then t = t+1 end
if t < 120 then h = true else h = false end if t < 120 and t > 0 then t1 = 1 else t1 = -1 end
output.getBool(1,h) output.getNumber(2,t1) output.getNumber(3,p1) output.getNumber(4,p2) end

A = false B = false function onTick() VTOL = input.getBool(1) OPEN = input.getBool(2)
if OPEN then A = true B = false elseif not OPEN then A = VTOL B = VTOL end
output.setBool(1, A) output.setBool(2, B) end

FOV = 0.6 function onTick() inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isP = input.getBool(1) gpsX = input.getNumber(7) gpsy = input.getNumber(8)
pFOV = isP and iPIR(inputX, inputY, 49, 24, 11, 10) -- + FOV iCAM = isP and iPIR(inputX, inputY, 49, 37, 11, 10) -- Toggle Infrared CAM mFOV = isP and iPIR(inputX, inputY, 49, 50, 11, 10) -- - FOV
if iCAM == nil then return false end if iCAM and not t then toggle = not toggle end t = iCAM
if pFOV and FOV < 0.95 then FOV = FOV + 0.01 elseif mFOV and FOV > 0.35 then FOV = FOV - 0.01 end
output.setBool(1, toggle) output.setNumber(1,FOV) end
function iPIR(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() screen.setColor(0,0,255,100)
screen.drawRect(49,24,11,10) -- + FOV screen.drawText(51,27,"+") screen.drawText(55,27,"F")
screen.drawRect(49,37,11,10) -- Toggle Infrared CAM screen.drawLine(54,40,57,40) screen.drawText(54,40,"I") screen.drawLine(54,44,57,44)
screen.drawRect(49,50,11,10) -- - FOV screen.drawText(51,53,"-") screen.drawText(55,53,"F") end

function onTick() isP = input.getBool(1)
Fuel = input.getNumber(7) Battery = input.getNumber(8) RPS = input.getNumber(9) ETA = input.getNumber(10)
if isP == nil then return false end if isP and not t then toggle = not toggle end t = isP end
function onDraw() if toggle then screen.drawText(2,2,"RPS:") screen.drawText(2,8,string.format("%.1f", RPS)) screen.drawText(2,17,"Elec:") screen.drawText(2,23,string.format("%.2f", Battery)) else if Fuel < 250 and Fuel > 0 then screen.setColor(255,255,0) elseif Fuel <= 0 then screen.setColor(255,0,0) end screen.drawText(2,8,string.format("%.1f", Fuel)) screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawText(2,2,"Fuel:") screen.drawText(2,17,"ETA:") screen.drawText(2,23,string.format("%.2f", ETA)) end end

function onTick() Speed = input.getNumber(7) Alt = input.getNumber(8) end
function onDraw() screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawText(2,2,"M/S:") screen.drawText(2,8,string.format("%.1f", Speed)) screen.drawText(2,17,"ALT:") if Alt < 100 and Alt > 0 then screen.setColor(255,255,0) elseif Alt < 0 then screen.setColor(255,0,0) end screen.drawText(2,23,string.format("%.1f", Alt)) end

object.script:
DT = 500 -- Distance To Target/Waypoint Before Switching VTOL function onTick() D = input.getNumber(1) VTOL = input.getBool(1) AP = input.getBool(2)
if AP and D < DT and not VTOL then OVTOL = true elseif AP and D > DT and VTOL then OVTOL = true else OVTOL = false end
output.setBool(1, OVTOL) end
